						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in a field on the road to Chaḷgēri.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇa II—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This broken and damaged inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kannaradēva.</hi> Only a portion of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king is preserved. In the absence of details it is difficult to identify the king. On the grounds of palaeography, however, the record may be ascribed to <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇa II.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
